    "Zeilberger (2016) extended MacMahon's work and generated the nondecreasing score sequences and their frequencies for n ≤ 15 using the Maple program.",
    "In a survey paper, Guy (1984) notes that Epstein's problem on r n (M 1) remains unsolved.",
    "In a recent publication, Malinovsky and Moon (2024) proved (2).",
    "They used a method which was introduced by Erdős and Wilson (1977) that considered the analogous problem for the vertices of maximum degree in a random labelled graph in which pairs of distinct vertices are joined by an edge with probability 1/2.",
